                <div class="hoang-titlecontent">
                    <span class="hoang-titleforhead">HEAD</span> <br>
                    <span class="hoang-maindescription">The Control Center, Life in Operation</span>
                    <div class="hoang-whitespace1"></div>
                </div>
                <div class="hoang-modau">
                    <div class="hoang-imgdescription" style="background-image: url(/testphp/images/BodyMapImages/hinh-anh-dau.jpg);"></div>
                    <div class="hoang-khaiquat">
                        <span id="hoang-titlekhainiem">CONCEPT</span> <br>
                        <div class="hoang-whitespace2"></div>
                        <p>
                            The human head is an important part of the body, containing many essential organs and structures necessary for life and daily activities. The human head has several crucial functions, including protecting the brain, facilitating the operation of the senses, and supporting communication.
                        </p>
                        
                    </div>
                </div>
                <div class="hoang-khainiem">
                    <span id="hoang-titlecautao">STRUCTURE</span>
                    <div class="hoang-whitespace3"></div>
                    <ol type="1">
                        <liz>
                            <b>Bone Structure</b>
                            <ul type="disc">
                                <li>
                                    <b>Cranial Bones</b>: Comprising multiple bones connected together, forming a solid protective box for the brain. The main bones include the frontal bone, parietal bones, occipital bone, temporal bones, and ethmoid bone.
                                </li>
                                <li>
                                    <b>Facial Bones</b>: Consisting of smaller bones such as the maxilla, mandible (the only movable bone), nasal bones, and zygomatic bones.
                                </li>
                            </ul>
                        </li>
                        <li>
                            <b>Brain</b>
                            <ul type="disc">
                                <li><b>Brain</b>: Protected by the skull, it is the control center of the nervous system. It regulates all body functions from sensation, movement, thought, emotion, to vital functions like respiration and circulation.</li>
                            </ul>
                        </li>
                        <li>
                            <b>Sensory Organs</b>
                            <ul type="disc">
                                <li><b>Eyes</b>: The organs of vision, allowing us to see the world around us.</li>
                                <li><b>Ears</b>: The organs of hearing, aiding in sound perception and balance maintenance.</li>
                                <li><b>Nose</b>: The organ of smell, aiding in olfaction and playing a role in respiration.</li>
                                <li><b>Mouth</b>: The organ of taste, containing the tongue which helps in tasting and participating in eating and communication.</li>
                            </ul>
                        </li>
                        <li>
                            <b>Muscles and Nerves</b>
                            <ul type="disc">
                                <li><b>Muscles</b>: Consisting of many small muscles that perform facial expressions like smiling, frowning, and talking.</li>
                                <li><b>Nerves</b>: Including many important nerves such as the facial nerve, optic nerve, and auditory nerve, controlling the sensation and movement of the head and face.</li>
                            </ul>
                        </li>
                        <li>
                            <b>Other Components</b>
                            <ul type="disc">
                                <li><b>Skin and Hair</b>: Protecting the head and helping in regulating body temperature.</li>
                                <li><b>Blood Vessels</b>: Providing blood and nutrients to the organs within the head.</li>
                            </ul>
                        </li>
                    </ol>
                </div>
